#29100
{C}Along The Thermodon River{c}~
{C}
   The Thermodon River directly to the west flows sluggishly
   here, near its mouth. A short distance to the north, it
   will empty into the Black Sea. The land here is well-fed
   by its waters, and lush green fields and forests abound.
   Many spectacular horses, alone or in packs, roam the land
   freely.
{c}
