#29102
{Y}A Trampled Path{y}~
{Y}
   The knee-high grass that grows here has been trampled down
   to bare dirt in places, forming a well-defined path that
   leads away from the eastern bank of the Thermodon. The
   large patches of brown among the dark green grass are proof
   that the path is used quite often. There is a dense forest
   in the valley to the south.
{y}
