#29128
{BLU}A Small Stall{blu}~
{BLU}
   This stall, one of the smallest in the market, is little
   more than a canvas stretched over four wooden poles. The
   merchant's fine armor, displayed somewhat carelessly on
   wooden benches, are mostly ignored by the market-goers.
   Surprising, considering his sturdy and well-crafted wares
   would be quite welcome in other markets. He should have
   known: Amazons disdain heavy armor, preferring freedom of
   movement over safety.
{blu}   
