{G}The Pasture{g}~
{GR}
   The land slopes gently up to a fertile field of ankle-high
   grass, which extend north all the way to the Black Sea. A
   herd of magnificent horses use these fields as grazing
   grounds, and they seem to have chased all other creatures
   out of the pasture. Most of the horses startle at human
   approach and so appear untamed, yet all of them are shoed.
{g}
