{BO,W}The Inner Sanctum{bo,w}~
{BO,W}
   The inner sanctum of the temple is a circular atrium about
   five paces wide. A round opening in the vaulted ceiling
   allows moonlight to shine upon the 25-foot tall statue of
   Artemis in the center of the room. Sacrifices to the
   goddess can be placed at a small altar at her feet. A
   walkway encircles the atrium and leads to the balcony.
{bo,w}
